    <stitle>MULTI-LINK FRONT AIR SUSPENSION - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - HEIGHT CONTROL VALVES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>HEIGHT CONTROL VALVES</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Both height control valves are removed in the same manner. Left side height control valve
                        shown.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Height Control Valves - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0301507" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301507.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Exhaust Air</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEIGHT CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BOLT AND WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. VALVE LEVER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain air from vehicle reservoirs.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolt, washer, nut, and height control rod from the valve lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the valve lever on the height control valve to EXH (exhaust) position to drain
                    air from system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0301508" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301508.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Height Control Valve Mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. AIR LINES</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TRANSVERSE CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MOUNT NUTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect two air lines from the height control valve.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three mount nuts from the height control valve and the transverse crossmember.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the height control valve.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Height Control Valves - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the height control valve on the transverse crossmember.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install three nuts on the height control valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301508">Figure 8, Items 1 and 4</hotlnk>). Torque nuts to 60 to 80 lbf-in (7 to 9
                    N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect two air lines to the height control valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301508">Figure 8, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the height control rod to the valve lever with the bolt, washer, and nut (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301507">Figure 7</hotlnk>). Torque bolt to 60 to 80 lbf-in (7 to 9 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check ride height and adjust as needed (refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03015_C01.xml" xrefid="c01">CHECKING RIDE HEIGHT</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
